- Try using std::single_view for Atom
#### dcmplx outside BasisSet
-Are the {ChargeDensity, Hamiltonian, Orbital, WaveFunction, SCFIterator} libraries ready for T=dcmplx?

- Next we need a highly trivial 1 electron (no ERIs yet) plane wave problem in order to get solids off the ground.
    Maybe just a hydrogen cubic lattice.  At high lattice spacing we know energy should be ~-0.5au/unit_cell (?)
- We have BlockQN in the Symmetry library for wave vector irreps.
- We have UnitCell and Lattice in the Structure library (maybe should be renamed Structure->Stucture even though Atom is normally 
    thought of as a structure).  
