## Clean up

- Simplify `LASolver` internals.
- Sort out PG cache — keep one cache in `DB_cache`.
- `constexpr` the static numeric lookup tables. `Fact`/`DFact`/`Twon` (`src/Common/Factorials.C`),
  `DoubleFactData` (PrimGaussian in `Radial/Imp/GaussianRF.C`), and the Pascal/binomial triangle
  (`src/BasisSet/Atom/Evaluators/Internal/PascalTriangle.C`) are pure integer/double recurrences of
  fixed size -> ideal for `constexpr std::array<double,N>` filled by a constexpr function (clean
  C++20, no container/JSON caveats). Three wins: removes the runtime "Initializing..." startup work;
  removes the forced-static-init-before-main hack (e.g. `static FactorialTables theFactoriTables`),
  which is the SAME static-init-order-fiasco class just fixed in PeriodicTable (mutable globals are
  zero-filled until that ctor runs); and turns mutable globals into immutable constants.
  Caveat: `Wigner3j`/`RelWigner3j` use sqrt of factorial ratios and `std::sqrt` isn't `constexpr`
  before C++26 -> need a hand-rolled constexpr sqrt (Newton) or keep those runtime for now.
- (Weaker, separate case) PeriodicTable Saito/NIST/DHF *data* is read from JSON at startup into static
  objects. NOT constexpr-parseable (`nlohmann::json` isn't constexpr; constexpr vector/string don't
  persist pre-C++23/26). If wanted, do it via a build-time JSON->codegen step emitting
  `constexpr std::array<Record,N>` + `std::string_view`. Motivation is robustness (kills the SIOF
  class + the COMMON_DATA_PATH runtime dependency), not speed. Cheaper interim: Meyers singletons.
- Home-grow Wigner symbols and drop the `wignerSymbols` submodule. Usage surface is tiny: only
  `wigner3j` + `clebschGordan` (no 6j/9j), in production just `RelAngularIntegrals.C` (DHF angular)
  plus `RelAngular.C` (which uses the submodule as a TEST ORACLE). CG is a 3j in disguise
  (CG = (-1)^(j1-j2+M) sqrt(2J+1) 3j(...)), so one correct `wigner3j` covers it. 3j is a finite
  factorial sum (Racah formula) -> trivial once `Fact[]` is constexpr (above). The rel calls pass
  RUNTIME k/kappa, so `std::sqrt` is fine there; a home-grown constexpr sqrt is the bonus that also
  lets the integer-l `Wigner3j.C` lookup table become a compile-time table (unifying both Wigner
  paths). Plan: write home-grown `wigner3j`, keep submodule as the oracle in `RelAngular.C` until it
  matches across all cases, THEN drop from production (and eventually the build). Risk: half-integer
  args + phase/selection conventions -- the existing oracle test de-risks it.
- `QchemTester::itsPT` (static `PeriodicTableSaito`): make it construct-on-first-use
  (`static const PeriodicTableSaito& PT(){ static const PeriodicTableSaito t; return t; }`), drop the
  static member, replace `itsPT.` with `PT().`. Do NOT move it to gtestmain.C like `theGlobalCache`:
  itsPT is immutable read-only (never reset, unlike the cache, which is main-managed precisely BECAUSE
  it's scrubbed between tests), AND `QchemTester` is also used by `scfrun.C` (a separate main) -- the
  gtestmain pattern would leave itsPT uninitialized there. (The SIOF crash itself is already fixed via
  the common_data_dir path; this is the remaining cleanliness step.)

